alcatelIND1OSPFMIB.description: This module describes an authoritative enterprise-specific Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMP) Management Information Base (MIB): For the Birds Of Prey Product Line Configuration Of Global OSPF Configuration Parameters. The right to make changes in specification and other information contained in this document without prior notice is reserved. No liability shall be assumed for any incidental, indirect, special, or consequential damages whatsoever arising from or related to this document or the information contained herein. Vendors, end-users, and other interested parties are granted non-exclusive license to use this specification in connection with management of the products for which it is intended to be used. AlaAuthenticationEncryptKey.name: AlaAuthenticationEncryptKey
AlaAuthenticationEncryptKey.description: The authentication encryption key that is used to decypher RIP simple passwords.

alaOspfRedistAdminStatus.name: alaOspfRedistAdminStatus
alaOspfRedistAdminStatus.description: Enable or disable redistribution of routes into OSPF. This object has been deprecated. Use the alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaOspfRedistRouteTag.name: alaOspfRedistRouteTag
alaOspfRedistRouteTag.description: A 32-bit value tagged to each OSPF internal route that is redistributed in to other routing protocol domains. The lower 16-bits typically indicate the autonomous system number.

alaOspfTimerSpfDelay.name: alaOspfTimerSpfDelay
alaOspfTimerSpfDelay.description: Number of seconds to delay the SPF calculation after receiving a topology change. This value should not be greater than SPF hold time.

alaOspfTimerSpfHold.name: alaOspfTimerSpfHold
alaOspfTimerSpfHold.description: Minimum time, in seconds, between two consecutive SPF calculations. This value should not be less than SPF delay time.

alaOspfRouteNumber.name: alaOspfRouteNumber
alaOspfRouteNumber.description: The number of network routes in OSPF routing table.

alaOspfMTUCheck.name: alaOspfMTUCheck
alaOspfMTUCheck.description: Enable or disable the check for MTU size in database description packets. Disabled by default

alaOspfAsBdrRtr.name: alaOspfAsBdrRtr
alaOspfAsBdrRtr.description: Enable or disable the switch being configured as an ASBR (Autonomous System Border Router. NOT SUPPORTED - Use IETF_OSPF.mib variable ospfASBdrRtrStatus.

alaOspfRedistProtoTable.name: alaOspfRedistProtoTable
alaOspfRedistProtoTable.description: Protocol based configuration for route redistribution using OSPF. This table has been deprecated. Use the alaRouteMapRedistProtoTable of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaOspfRedistProtoEntry.name: alaOspfRedistProtoEntry
alaOspfRedistProtoEntry.description: A range of routes from a protocol to be redistributed using OSPF. This entry has been deprecated. Use the alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaOspfRedistProtoId.name: alaOspfRedistProtoId
alaOspfRedistProtoId.description: The routing mechanism via which the routes, to be redistributed using OSPF, are learned. This object has been deprecated. Use the alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaOspfRedistProtoSubnets.name: alaOspfRedistProtoSubnets
alaOspfRedistProtoSubnets.description: Enable/disable the reditribution of subnet routes. Default value is enable. This object has been deprecated. Use the alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaOspfRedistProtoMetricType.name: alaOspfRedistProtoMetricType
alaOspfRedistProtoMetricType.description: Type of metric to be used for redistribution. This object has been deprecated. Use the alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaOspfRedistProtoMetric.name: alaOspfRedistProtoMetric
alaOspfRedistProtoMetric.description: Default metric to be used for redistributing routes using type1 metric type. This object has been deprecated. Use the alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaOspfRedistProtoStatus.name: alaOspfRedistProtoStatus
alaOspfRedistProtoStatus.description: Row status of this entry. This object has been deprecated. Use the alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaOspfRedistProtoRouteTag.name: alaOspfRedistProtoRouteTag
alaOspfRedistProtoRouteTag.description: Associated route tag. This object has been deprecated.

alaOspfRouteTable.name: alaOspfRouteTable
alaOspfRouteTable.description: OSPF routing table which contains the network routes.

alaOspfRouteEntry.name: alaOspfRouteEntry
alaOspfRouteEntry.description: OSPF routing table which contains the network routes.

alaOspfRouteDest.name: alaOspfRouteDest
alaOspfRouteDest.description: The destination IP address of this route.

alaOspfRouteMask.name: alaOspfRouteMask
alaOspfRouteMask.description: The network mask for this route.

alaOspfRouteTos.name: alaOspfRouteTos
alaOspfRouteTos.description: Type Of Service (TOS) for this route.

alaOspfRouteNextHop.name: alaOspfRouteNextHop
alaOspfRouteNextHop.description: The address of the next hop to reach this route.

alaOspfRouteIfIndex.name: alaOspfRouteIfIndex
alaOspfRouteIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value which identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached.

alaOspfRouteAge.name: alaOspfRouteAge
alaOspfRouteAge.description: The number of seconds since this route was last updated or otherwise determined to be correct.

alaOspfRouteTag.name: alaOspfRouteTag
alaOspfRouteTag.description: The associated route tag for external roues. It's 0 for routes internal to the autonomous system.

alaOspfRouteMetric1.name: alaOspfRouteMetric1
alaOspfRouteMetric1.description: The primary routing metric for this route.

alaOspfRouteMetric2.name: alaOspfRouteMetric2
alaOspfRouteMetric2.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. It's 0 for internal routes. For an external route, it's the metric to reach the ASBR that announced the external route.

alaOspfRouteStatus.name: alaOspfRouteStatus
alaOspfRouteStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions.

alaOspfBdrRouterTable.name: alaOspfBdrRouterTable
alaOspfBdrRouterTable.description: OSPF routing table which contains the routes to border (ABR and ASBR) routers.

alaOspfBdrRouterEntry.name: alaOspfBdrRouterEntry
alaOspfBdrRouterEntry.description: OSPF routing table which contains the routes to border (ABR and ASBR) routers.

alaOspfBdrRouterAreaId.name: alaOspfBdrRouterAreaId
alaOspfBdrRouterAreaId.description: The area to which the border router belongs to.

alaOspfBdrRouterId.name: alaOspfBdrRouterId
alaOspfBdrRouterId.description: The router idenitifer of this border router.

alaOspfBdrRouterTos.name: alaOspfBdrRouterTos
alaOspfBdrRouterTos.description: Type Of Service (TOS) for this route.

alaOspfBdrRouterNextHop.name: alaOspfBdrRouterNextHop
alaOspfBdrRouterNextHop.description: The address of the next hop to reach this border router.

alaOspfBdrRouterIfIndex.name: alaOspfBdrRouterIfIndex
alaOspfBdrRouterIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value which identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached.

alaOspfBdrRouterAge.name: alaOspfBdrRouterAge
alaOspfBdrRouterAge.description: The number of seconds since this route was last updated or otherwise determined to be correct.

alaOspfBdrRouterMetric.name: alaOspfBdrRouterMetric
alaOspfBdrRouterMetric.description: The cost to reach the border router.

alaOspfBdrRouterStatus.name: alaOspfBdrRouterStatus
alaOspfBdrRouterStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions.

alaOspfRedistRouteTable.name: alaOspfRedistRouteTable
alaOspfRedistRouteTable.description: A configuration table which controls the routes to be redistributed by OSPF from other routing protocols. This table has been deprecated. Use the alaRouteMapRedistProtoTable of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaOspfRedistRouteEntry.name: alaOspfRedistRouteEntry
alaOspfRedistRouteEntry.description: A configuration table which controls the routes to be redistributed by OSPF from other routing protocols. This entry has been deprecated. Use the alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaOspfRedistRouteProto.name: alaOspfRedistRouteProto
alaOspfRedistRouteProto.description: Protocol from which this route is to be imported into OSPF. This object has been deprecated. Use the alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaOspfRedistRouteDest.name: alaOspfRedistRouteDest
alaOspfRedistRouteDest.description: The destination IP address of this route. This object has been deprecated. Use the alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaOspfRedistRouteMask.name: alaOspfRedistRouteMask
alaOspfRedistRouteMask.description: The network mask for this route. This object has been deprecated. Use the alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaOspfRedistRouteMetric.name: alaOspfRedistRouteMetric
alaOspfRedistRouteMetric.description: The metric to be used for the redistributed route. This object has been deprecated. Use the alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaOspfRedistRouteControl.name: alaOspfRedistRouteControl
alaOspfRedistRouteControl.description: Specifies how routes matching this entry are to be redistributed into OSPF. The different mechanisms possible are to redistribute all the subnet routes, redistribute an aggregated route if there are one or more actual routes which match this entry or redistribute only an exactly matching route. This object has been deprecated. Use the alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaOspfRedistRouteTagMatch.name: alaOspfRedistRouteTagMatch
alaOspfRedistRouteTagMatch.description: Redistribute the route only when the route tag matches with this value. It defaults to 0 which matches all route tags. This object has been deprecated. Use the alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaOspfRedistRouteEffect.name: alaOspfRedistRouteEffect
alaOspfRedistRouteEffect.description: Specifies whether the redistribution of routes in this range is allowed or denied. This object has been deprecated. Use the alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaOspfRedistRouteStatus.name: alaOspfRedistRouteStatus
alaOspfRedistRouteStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to row installation and removal conventions. This object has been deprecated. Use the alaRouteMapRedistProtoEntry objects of AlcatelIND1RouteMap.mib.

alaOspfIfMd5Table.name: alaOspfIfMd5Table
alaOspfIfMd5Table.description: The OSPF Interface MD5 Table describes the MD5 key management for OSPF interfaces.

alaOspfIfMd5Entry.name: alaOspfIfMd5Entry
alaOspfIfMd5Entry.description: The OSPF Interface MD5 Entry describes the MD5 key management for OSPF interfaces.

alaOspfIfMd5IpAddress.name: alaOspfIfMd5IpAddress
alaOspfIfMd5IpAddress.description: The IP address of this OSPF MD5 key interface.

alaOspfIfMd5KeyId.name: alaOspfIfMd5KeyId
alaOspfIfMd5KeyId.description: A key identifier which identifies the algorithm and MD5 secret key associated with this interface.

alaOspfIfMd5KeyStartAccept.name: alaOspfIfMd5KeyStartAccept
alaOspfIfMd5KeyStartAccept.description: The time that OSPF router will start accepting packets that have been created with this key.

alaOspfIfMd5KeyStopAccept.name: alaOspfIfMd5KeyStopAccept
alaOspfIfMd5KeyStopAccept.description: The time that OSPF router will stop accepting packets that have been created with this key.

alaOspfIfMd5KeyStartGenerate.name: alaOspfIfMd5KeyStartGenerate
alaOspfIfMd5KeyStartGenerate.description: The time that OSPF router will start using this key for packet generation.

alaOspfIfMd5KeyStopGenerate.name: alaOspfIfMd5KeyStopGenerate
alaOspfIfMd5KeyStopGenerate.description: The time that OSPF router will stop using this key for packet generation.

alaOspfIfMd5EncryptKey.name: alaOspfIfMd5EncryptKey
alaOspfIfMd5EncryptKey.description: The MD5 message digest Encrypted key.

alaOspfIfEncryptKey.name: alaOspfIfEncryptKey
alaOspfIfEncryptKey.description: The authentication encryption key that is used to decypher OSPF passwords.

alaOspfIfIpMask.name: alaOspfIfIpMask
alaOspfIfIpMask.description: The IP mask of this OSPF interface.

alaOspfIfVlanId.name: alaOspfIfVlanId
alaOspfIfVlanId.description: Vlan Identifier associated with this interface

alaOspfIfDrRouterid.name: alaOspfIfDrRouterid
alaOspfIfDrRouterid.description: Router Id of Designated router for this interface

alaOspfIfBdrRouterid.name: alaOspfIfBdrRouterid
alaOspfIfBdrRouterid.description: Router Id of Backup Designated router for this interface

alaOspfIfMTU.name: alaOspfIfMTU
alaOspfIfMTU.description: Max Transfer size of OSPF packets on this interface

alaOspfIfInitNbrs.name: alaOspfIfInitNbrs
alaOspfIfInitNbrs.description: Number of ospf INIT state neighbors on this interface

alaOspfIfExchNbrs.name: alaOspfIfExchNbrs
alaOspfIfExchNbrs.description: Number of ospf EXCHANGE state neighbors on this interface

alaOspfIfFullNbrs.name: alaOspfIfFullNbrs
alaOspfIfFullNbrs.description: Number of ospf FULL state neighbors on this interface

alaOspfIfLinkType.name: alaOspfIfLinkType
alaOspfIfLinkType.description: Type of physical medium used for transmission of OSPF packets

alaOspfIfIntfName.name: alaOspfIfIntfName
alaOspfIfIntfName.description: The user defined name used to identify the IP interface

alaOspfIf2WayNbrs.name: alaOspfIf2WayNbrs
alaOspfIf2WayNbrs.description: Number of ospf 2-WAY state neighbors on this interface

alaOspfIfBfdStatus.name: alaOspfIfBfdStatus
alaOspfIfBfdStatus.description: Enables/Disables OSPF for a BFD interface

alaOspfIfBfdDrsOnly.name: alaOspfIfBfdDrsOnly
alaOspfIfBfdDrsOnly.description: Enables/Disables Drs Only option for a BFD interface

alaOspfVirtIfEncryptKey.name: alaOspfVirtIfEncryptKey
alaOspfVirtIfEncryptKey.description: The authentication encryption key that is used to decypher OSPF passwords.

alaOspfVirtIfOperStatus.name: alaOspfVirtIfOperStatus
alaOspfVirtIfOperStatus.description: Operational status of the virtual link

alaOspfRestartHelperSupport.name: alaOspfRestartHelperSupport
alaOspfRestartHelperSupport.description: The router's support for acting as an OSPF hitless restart helper.

alaOspfRestartHelperStrictLSAChecking.name: alaOspfRestartHelperStrictLSAChecking
alaOspfRestartHelperStrictLSAChecking.description: Indicates whether or not a changed LSA will result in termination of graceful restart by a helping router.

alaOspfRestartHelperStatus.name: alaOspfRestartHelperStatus
alaOspfRestartHelperStatus.description: Indicates whether this OSPF router is operating as a Helper to a restarting router.

alaOspfRFC1583Compatibility.name: alaOspfRFC1583Compatibility
alaOspfRFC1583Compatibility.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 16.4.1 External path preferences
alaOspfRFC1583Compatibility.description: Indicates metrics used to choose among multiple AS- external-LSAs. When RFC1583Compatibility is set to enabled, only cost will be used when choosing among multiple AS-external-LSAs advertising the same destination. When RFC1583Compatibility is set to disabled, preference will be driven first by type of path using cost only to break ties.

alaOspfOpaqueLsaSupport.name: alaOspfOpaqueLsaSupport
alaOspfOpaqueLsaSupport.description: The router's support for Opaque LSA types.

alaOspfTrafficEngineeringSupport.name: alaOspfTrafficEngineeringSupport
alaOspfTrafficEngineeringSupport.description: The router's support for OSPF traffic engineering.

alaOspfReferenceBandwidth.name: alaOspfReferenceBandwidth
alaOspfReferenceBandwidth.description: Reference bandwidth in kilobits/second for calculating default interface metrics. The default value is 100,000 KBPS (100 MBPS)

alaOspfRestartSupport.name: alaOspfRestartSupport
alaOspfRestartSupport.description: The router's support for OSPF hitless restart. Options include: no restart support, only planned restarts or both planned and unplanned restarts.

alaOspfRestartInterval.name: alaOspfRestartInterval
alaOspfRestartInterval.description: Configured OSPF hitless restart timeout interval.

alaOspfRestartStatus.name: alaOspfRestartStatus
alaOspfRestartStatus.description: Current status of OSPF hitless restart. The status of hitless restart is unplannedRestart after a CMM takeover. Before CMM takeover, the status is plannedRestart.

alaOspfRestartAge.name: alaOspfRestartAge
alaOspfRestartAge.description: Remaining time in current OSPF hitless restart interval.

alaOspfRestartExitReason.name: alaOspfRestartExitReason
alaOspfRestartExitReason.description: Describes the outcome of the last attempt at a hitless restart. If the value is 'none', no restart has yet been attempted. If the value is 'inProgress', a restart attempt is currently underway.

alaOspfNbrRestartHelperStatus.name: alaOspfNbrRestartHelperStatus
alaOspfNbrRestartHelperStatus.description: Indicates whether the router is acting as a hitless restart helper for the neighbor.

alaOspfNbrRestartHelperAge.name: alaOspfNbrRestartHelperAge
alaOspfNbrRestartHelperAge.description: Remaining time in current OSPF hitless restart interval, if the router is acting as a restart helper for the neighbor.

alaOspfNbrRestartHelperExitReason.name: alaOspfNbrRestartHelperExitReason
alaOspfNbrRestartHelperExitReason.description: Describes the outcome of the last attempt at acting as a hitless restart helper for the neighbor.

alaOspfNbrAreaId.name: alaOspfNbrAreaId
alaOspfNbrAreaId.description: The area to which this neighbor belongs

alaOspfNbrBdrAddress.name: alaOspfNbrBdrAddress
alaOspfNbrBdrAddress.description: Backup Designated router of this neighbor

alaOspfNbrType.name: alaOspfNbrType
alaOspfNbrType.description: Neighbors learned via the OSPF Hello protocol are dynamic. Configured neighbors are static

alaOspfNbrMode.name: alaOspfNbrMode
alaOspfNbrMode.description: Current neighbor mode. This is applicable only during adjacency formation

alaOspfNbrMd5SeqNo.name: alaOspfNbrMd5SeqNo
alaOspfNbrMd5SeqNo.description: Sequence number used in Md5 authentication

alaOspfNbrLastHello.name: alaOspfNbrLastHello
alaOspfNbrLastHello.description: No of seconds elapsed since the last hello was received from this neighbor

alaOspfNbrPendingLSreq.name: alaOspfNbrPendingLSreq
alaOspfNbrPendingLSreq.description: Number of outstanding link state requests to be sent to this neighbor

alaOspfNbrPendingLSack.name: alaOspfNbrPendingLSack
alaOspfNbrPendingLSack.description: Number of outstanding link state acknowledgements to be sent to this neighbor

alaOspfNbrPendingLSupd.name: alaOspfNbrPendingLSupd
alaOspfNbrPendingLSupd.description: Number of outstanding link state update packets to be sent to this neighbor

alaOspfVirtNbrAugEntry.name: alaOspfVirtNbrAugEntry
alaOspfVirtNbrAugEntry.reference: OSPF Version 2 Management Information Base, Work In Progress draft-ietf-ospf-mib-update-07.txt Section B.4

alaOspfAreaNssaTranslatorRole.name: alaOspfAreaNssaTranslatorRole
alaOspfAreaNssaTranslatorRole.description: Specifies whether or not an NSSA border router will unconditionally translate Type-7 LSAs into Type-5 LSAs. When set to always, an NSSA border router always translates Type-7 LSAs into Type-5 LSAs regardless of the translator state of other NSSA border routers. When set to candidate, an NSSA border router participates in the translator election process. For non-NSSA border routers, this value is none.

alaOspfAreaNssaTranslatorStabilityInterv.name: alaOspfAreaNssaTranslatorStabilityInterval
alaOspfAreaNssaTranslatorStabilityInterv.description: Defines the length of time (in seconds) an elected Type-7 translator will continue to perform its translator duties once it has determined that its translator status has been deposed by another NSSA border router translator. For non-NSSA border routers, this value is not defined and will be 0.

alaOspfAreaNssaImportSetPbit.name: alaOspfAreaNssaImportSetPbit
alaOspfAreaNssaImportSetPbit.description: Specifies whether or not an NSSA AS boundary router sets the P-bit when external routes are imported into the NSSA as Type-7 LSAs. For non-NSSA boundary routers, this value is not defined and will be none.

alaOspfAreaNssaTranslatorState.name: alaOspfAreaNssaTranslatorState

alaOspfDefaultOriginate.name: alaOspfDefaultOriginate
alaOspfDefaultOriginate.description: Indicates whether this ASBR router originates the default route into the OSPF normal area(s). If set to 'only', the default route is advertised into the OSPF normal area, provided the ASBR has a route to 0.0.0.0/0 in its routing table. Alternatively, if set to 'always', a default route is advertised into the OSPF domain regardless of whether the ASBR has a route to 0.0.0.0/0. A value of 'none' has the effect of not originating the default route.
